URL security analysis for shell environments

Usage: tirith <COMMAND>

Commands:
  daemon      Manage the tirith background daemon
  check       Check a command for URL security issues before execution
  paste       Check pasted content for security issues
  run         Safely download and execute a script
  score       Score a URL for security risk
  diff        Compare a URL against known-good patterns
  explain     Show documentation for a detection rule
  why         Explain the last triggered rule
  receipt     Manage execution receipts
  checkpoint  Manage file checkpoints for rollback (experimental)
  init        Initialize tirith shell hooks
  scan        Scan files for hidden content and config poisoning
  fetch       Check a URL for server-side cloaking (different content for bots vs browsers)
  mcp-server  Run as MCP server (JSON-RPC over stdio)
  gateway     MCP gateway proxy — intercepts shell tool calls for security analysis
  setup       Configure tirith protection for an AI coding tool
  policy      Manage security policies
  audit       Audit log management: export, stats, compliance reports (Team)
  activate    Activate a license key
  license     Show or manage license status
  trust       Manage trusted patterns (allowlist entries with TTL, scoping, and audit)
  warnings    Show accumulated session warnings
  threat-db   Manage the threat intelligence database
  doctor      Diagnose tirith installation and configuration
  help        Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
